I once (briefly) tried to collaborate with someone who would not use `else if` statements, and used braces always even if they were optional.<p><pre><code>    if (foo) {
        <whatever>
    } else {
        if (bar) {
        <whatever>
        } else {
            if (baz) {
            <whatever>
            } else {
                if (spam) {
                    <whatever>
                } else {
                    ...
                    <etc>
                }
            }
        } 
    }
</code></pre>
It didn&#x27;t end well.<p>He also wouldn&#x27;t use break or continue or multiple returns.<p>As this article says, it led to really really annoying-to-read code.
